HEADWORD: Tangly
<hw>Tan"gly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Entangled;
intricate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Covered with tangle, or seaweed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Prone, helpless, on the <qex>tangly</qex> beach he lay.</q>
<rj><qau>Falconer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tango</ent>⟦br⟧
